# Project Context

Before working on any task, read the relevant files from the `docs/` folder to understand the project:

- `docs/overview.md` — what the project is, audience, key features, tech stack
- `docs/architecture.md` — system architecture, monorepo structure, services
- `docs/features/` — feature descriptions and flows
- `docs/api/` — API contracts
- `docs/decisions/` — architectural decision records (ADRs)

Always reference this documentation when making architectural decisions or implementing features.
When the user describes something new, suggest updating the relevant doc file.
